00:00:45.720 --> 00:00:49.580
they open up an entire new window on the
universe, everything, almost everything we've done

00:00:49.610 --> 00:00:54.640
in astronomy, barring a few cosmic rays
and neutrinos, has been mediated through

00:00:54.640 --> 00:00:57.890
light - we've used light to figure out
what's going on in the universe. Having

00:00:57.890 --> 00:01:01.489
an entirely new way of detecting what's
going on out there in the universe is a

00:01:01.489 --> 00:01:05.132
very exciting thing for astronomers
because it - it opens up all sorts of new avenues for

00:01:05.160 --> 00:01:06.360
us to pursue on research.

00:01:06.360 --> 00:01:13.400
As the Earth goes around the Sun then the spacetime is distorting around the Earth

00:01:13.400 --> 00:01:17.160
and that's propagating out in waves in all directions.

