going at close to the speed of light.
So the the spacetime in which it's

00:06:10.419 --> 00:06:15.729
revolving must be going - is having huge distortions
associated with it.

00:06:15.729 --> 00:06:20.069
And so it begins to send out
gravitational waves - they've been happening

00:06:20.069 --> 00:06:22.900
all the time but at a much lower
amplitude because they've not been

00:06:22.900 --> 00:06:28.840
feeling this effect, like this. And then these two black holes keep coming in together and they merge.

00:06:29.640 --> 00:06:33.060
And what happens is when you've got two black holes they'll merge into a bigger black hole.

00:06:33.240 --> 00:06:36.940
So one of them is 29 solar masses,
the other one is 36 solar masses.

00:06:37.020 --> 00:06:41.379
If you add those two together you get 65 solar
masses, so you would think by merging

00:06:41.379 --> 00:06:45.539
these two together you make a 65 solar mass
black hole. Turns out they can also tell

00:06:45.539 --> 00:06:48.999
you what the mass of the black hole ended up
with was. Again, just by looking at the

00:06:49.000 --> 00:06:53.200
kind of signal, and it's not 65 solar masses, it's about 62 solar masses.

00:06:53.720 --> 00:06:58.639
And the reason why is because three solar
masses has disappeared, and via Einstein's

00:06:58.639 --> 00:07:02.069
famous formula E=mc^2
those three solar masses of energy

00:07:02.620 --> 00:07:06.509
have all been turned into the energy of
the gravitational waves. So three solar masses

00:07:06.509 --> 00:07:10.770
by E=mc^2 has been turned
into a huge amount of energy liberated

00:07:10.770 --> 00:07:16.129
in this gravitational wave explosion. And in
fact if you work out what the luminosity

00:07:16.139 --> 00:07:20.060
of the thing was, how bright it was in
gravitational waves, in that fraction of a

00:07:20.060 --> 00:07:24.129
second as all this happened, it was
brighter, it was liberating more energy,

00:07:24.129 --> 00:07:28.769
more power than all the stars in the entire observable
universe -

00:07:28.769 --> 00:07:31.769
for that fraction of a second - all in gravitational waves.

00:07:32.320 --> 00:07:37.340
But there was no light?
-There may well have been some light as well, but that

00:07:37.360 --> 00:07:40.010
was just what was coming out in
gravitational waves, mostly the energy

00:07:40.020 --> 00:07:43.160
of this merger was coming out in these sudden bursts of gravitational waves.

00:07:43.160 --> 00:07:44.610
They're traveling now,

00:07:44.610 --> 00:07:48.659
they've got a billion years, they're traveling in all
directions - they propagate, and then it - as it

00:07:48.669 --> 00:07:54.129
happens, there's a detector - two detectors
in America, been recently updated, and

00:07:54.129 --> 00:07:57.220
they've just been turned on - they were doing
I think they call it the engineering run - they

00:07:57.229 --> 00:07:59.889
haven't even started doing the proper
science run.

00:07:59.889 --> 00:08:05.159
They'd been turned on for a few weeks, and a few
billion years later these waves are

00:08:05.159 --> 00:08:08.919
coming through - now they've lost a lot of
their energy, right? Just as light loses

00:08:08.919 --> 00:08:14.719
its energy and becomes dimmer
and dimmer. The huge amplitude associated

00:08:14.719 --> 00:08:18.509
with the waves early on is now dimmed down, down, down, down. They pass through

00:08:18.509 --> 00:08:23.979
this detector, and the detector consists
of two arms - four kilometer long arms.

00:08:23.979 --> 00:08:27.159
An interferometer, classic interferometer
has two arms to it and you basically

00:08:27.159 --> 00:08:32.250
shine a light down each arm - usually a laser 'cause you want it to be nice coherent light - and

00:08:32.250 --> 00:08:37.630
in essence you shine the light backwards and forwards along each of these arms - by recombining the light you

00:08:37.630 --> 00:08:40.829
can essentially tune the thing so
that the two arms are exactly the same

00:08:40.829 --> 00:08:45.829
length as each other. And if you set up
your interferometer right, then the light

00:08:45.829 --> 00:08:49.069
that's gone down this arm, and the light
that goes down this arm exactly cancel

00:08:49.069 --> 00:08:53.310
each other out so you end up with no
signal at all. And so that's a thing called

00:08:53.310 --> 00:08:56.899
a nulling interferometer it's set to - you get zero
signal when the two arms are actually

00:08:56.899 --> 00:09:01.279
tuned in that way. Now, of course, when one
of these waves goes past, in one

00:09:01.280 --> 00:09:05.440
direction it actually causes a contraction and in
the other direction it actually causes an expansion.

00:09:05.820 --> 00:09:09.620
"This back and forth stretching
and squeezing happens over and over

00:09:09.620 --> 00:09:11.620
until the wave has passed."

00:09:11.620 --> 00:09:14.520
As the wave
goes past, by this tiny, tiny amount

00:09:14.529 --> 00:09:18.029
the arms will no longer be exactly the
same length - and the effect of that is

00:09:18.029 --> 00:09:21.779
then that exact cancellation ceases to
work, and suddenly some of the light gets

00:09:21.780 --> 00:09:24.870
through your interferometer. So the way they
actually detect it is that they actually

00:09:24.870 --> 00:09:29.240
start seeing light in the interferometer
because the arms have changed in length by

00:09:29.240 --> 00:09:32.949
that tiny amount.
-This huge amount of energy required

00:09:34.279 --> 00:09:40.839
this desperately accurate detector in order
to be able to find the gravitational

00:09:40.840 --> 00:09:45.820
waves. And then you might ask: "How do you
