the same profile -

00:11:10.790 --> 00:11:15.720
7 milliseconds later which corresponds
to the light travel time - and that

00:11:15.720 --> 00:11:21.480
enabled them to sort of give an estimate of
where in the sky this original thing had started from.

00:11:21.480 --> 00:11:23.760
So for example this
thing that they've detected, they know it's

00:11:23.769 --> 00:11:26.399
somewhere in the southern hemisphere.
